    dc:title "Four new species of polychromatic spiny-tailed iguanian lizards, genus Stenocercus (Iguania: Tropiduridae), from Peru" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345990>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345994>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345988> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345990>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Stenocercus leybachi sp. nov. preserved holotype, adult male, SVL 83 mm (CORBIDI 16397): dorsal (A), lateral (B), and ventral (C) views of the head; dorsal (D) and ventral (E) views of the entire specimen. Photographs by LAGA. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6345990/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345994>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Dorsolateral and ventral views of Stenocercus leybachi sp. nov. in life: (A-C) holotype, SVL 83 mm (CORBIDI 16397); (D, E) adult male, SVL 84 mm (CORBIDI 16532); (F, G) adult male, SVL 81 mm (CORBIDI 13333); (H) adult female, SVL 82 mm (CORBIDI 16400); (I, J) adult female, SVL 80 mm (CORBIDI 16429); (K) adult male hidden in a tree hole (not collected); (L) adult female photographed hidden in a hollow branch (not collected). Photographs by (A-C, & H) D. Vásquez, (D, E, & I-L) JCCA, and (F, G) V. Duran." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6345994/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345988>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Stenocercus asenlignus sp. nov., Stenocercus leybachi sp. nov., S. nigrocaudatus sp. nov., and S. qalaywasi sp. nov., and the similar species: S. arndti, S. carrioni, S. chlorostictus, S. crassicaudatus, S. empetrus, S. eunetopsis, S. flagracanthus, S. simonsii, and S. torquatus. The symbols of species with a black spot in the centre correspond to type localities. Black dots correspond to important cities for reference." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6345988/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

